## The Arctic Framework

There is one more piece worth naming directly: the Arctic Framework.

These are the absolute red lines — the actions the system will never take regardless of instruction, context, or apparent justification:

- No silent autonomy — the system does not act without the operator’s awareness
- No covert channels — no hidden communication pathways
- No hidden networking — the system does not reach out without authorization
- No unbounded recursion — no self-amplifying loops without a hard limit
- No operator override — the human retains final authority
- No real-world control — the system does not acquire control over physical systems without explicit human authorization

These are not configurable. They are not softened by context. They are the floor beneath the floor — the constraints that hold even when everything else is under pressure.

This is what “Human Primacy” means in practice. Not as a value. As architecture.

