## What Comes Next

PantheonOS is open source — Apache 2.0 with a commercial dual license. The decision to open-source it was deliberate and considered. Keeping it proprietary would create exactly the kind of asymmetric capability concentration the system is designed to prevent.

The work continues. The Star Act advocacy campaign — supporting H.R. 2102 / S. 1032, ending concurrent receipt offsets for combat-injured veterans — runs on the same propagation infrastructure. Governance is not a domain. It is a discipline. It applies to institutions as much as to software.

If you are building agentic AI systems and you don’t have a Gate, you should ask yourself what happens when your system acts on a misunderstanding at 3am and there is no human in the loop to catch it.

PantheonOS was built for that question.

The repo is open. The DOI is timestamped. The invariants are public.

